 <text>
  <front>
   <head>A SUMMER EVENING.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">HOW fine has the Day been, how bright was the Sun,</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">How lovely and joyful the Course that he run,</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Tho' he rose in a Mist when his Race he begun,</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And there follow'd some Droppings of Rain!</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">But now the fair Traveller's come to the West,</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">His Rays are all Gold, and his Beauties are best;</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">He paints the Sky gay as he sinks to his Rest,</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And foretels a bright Rising again.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="9" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Just such is the Christian: His Course he begins,</l>
     <l n="10" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Like the Sun in a Mist, while he mourns for his Sins,</l>
     <l n="11" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">And melts into Tears: Then he breaks out and shines,</l>
     <l n="12" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And travels his heav'nly Way:</l>
     <l n="13" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">But when he comes nearer to finish his Race,</l>
     <l n="14" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Like a fine setting Sun he looks richer in Grace,</l>
     <l n="15" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">And gives a sure Hope at the End of his Days</l>
     <l n="16" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Of rising in brighter Array.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
